Appendix G: Up-down asymmetry, chirality and planar-chirality of surfaces
We discuss here the symmetries of a surface with rotational symmetry in the plane. The symmetries that can be broken for to these surfaces are the up-down mirror symmetry (Mn), the mirror symmetries in the plane (Mt, a mirror symmetry by a plane going along an arbitrary tangent vector t), and the up-down rotation symmetries (Rt, a rotation of π around an arbitrary tangent vector t). Rotations around the normal with angle π, Rn preserve the state of a surface with rotational symmetry in the plane. Composition of these symmetries are indicated in the multiplication table II.
